<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc02e64aa-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s17202"><num value="17202">§ 17202.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated to the Secretary to carry out the programs under this part $170,000,000 for each of fiscal years 2021 through 2025.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc02e64ab-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/110/140/tVI/s623">Pub. L. 110–140, title VI, § 623</ref>, <date date="2007-12-19">Dec. 19, 2007</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/121/1684">121 Stat. 1684</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/116/260/dZ/tIII/s3002/j">Pub. L. 116–260, div. Z, title III, § 3002(j)</ref>, <date date="2020-12-27">Dec. 27, 2020</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/134/2495">134 Stat. 2495</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc02e64ac-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idc02e64ad-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idc02e64ae-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2020—<ref href="/us/pl/116/260">Pub. L. 116–260</ref> amended section generally. Prior to amendment, section related to authorization of appropriations for fiscal years 2008 to 2012.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idc02e64af-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idc02e64b0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective on the date that is 1 day after <date date="2007-12-19">Dec. 19, 2007</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/110/140/s1601">section 1601 of Pub. L. 110–140</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t2/s1824">section 1824 of Title 2</ref>, The Congress.</p>
</note>
